description:
Create the detector trait framework in analysis/src/board_analysis/detector.rs (new file).

Structs/traits:
- TacticalContext<'a> { before: &Board, after: &Board, mv: Option<Move>, side_to_move_before: Color, before_attacks: &AttackMap, after_attacks: &AttackMap, eval_before: Option<i32>, eval_after: Option<i32>, best_line: Option<Vec<String>> }
- trait TacticalDetector { fn detect(&self, ctx: &TacticalContext) -> Vec<TacticalTag>; }

The context carries both positions + attack maps + optional engine info. Each detector is a zero-sized struct implementing the trait. The pipeline calls detect() on each registered detector and collects all tags.

Depends on: ct-2f00bfc6 (TacticalTag model), ct-9f92e422 (AttackMap).

## What
Scaffold the new `chesstty` binary crate that serves as the single entry point for the application. Implement the clap-based CLI with two modes: default (no args) launches server+TUI, and the `engine stop` subcommand signals the server to shut down.

## File(s)
- `chesstty/chesstty/Cargo.toml` (new)
- `chesstty/chesstty/src/main.rs` (new)
- `chesstty/chesstty/src/cli.rs` (new)
- `Cargo.toml` (add `chesstty` to workspace members)

## Implementation Details
```rust
use clap::{Parser, Subcommand};

#[derive(Parser)]
#[command(name = "chesstty", about = "Chess TUI with integrated engine analysis")]
struct Cli {
    #[command(subcommand)]
    command: Option<Commands>,
}

#[derive(Subcommand)]
enum Commands {
    /// Manage the engine server
    Engine {
        #[command(subcommand)]
        action: EngineAction,
    },
}

#[derive(Subcommand)]
enum EngineAction {
    /// Stop the background engine server
    Stop {
        /// Force immediate shutdown (SIGKILL instead of SIGTERM)
        #[arg(short, long)]
        force: bool,
    },
}
```

- Default (None): orchestrate server launch + TUI (implementation in later task)
- `engine stop`: signal server shutdown (implementation in later task)
- main.rs: match on cli.command, dispatch to handler stubs

## Dependencies
- clap = { version = "4", features = ["derive"] }
- tokio = { version = "1.41", features = ["full"] }
- anyhow = "1.0"
- tracing, tracing-subscriber

